Loop::Flow::Object

Looping code of one object with forking on/off. Simple switch and count of forks.
Executing code, control count and exit from loop by the object methods.


DEPEND

    For forks: use POSIX ':sys_wait_h'; # для waitpid -1, WNOHANG;

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Loop::Flow::Object

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Loop-Flow

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Loop-Flow

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Loop-Flow

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Loop-Flow/


